    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-04-24T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-04-24T08:00:00-05:00" n="256"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d256">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.744/21: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kodding</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-24T15:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 24, 1929—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. Department’s instruction No. 278, January 9th. The Bulgarian Government
                    releases former Bulgarians from military fines from the date of their
                    acquisition of residence in the United States, but does not release them from
                    road repair and other personal taxes accrued previous to naturalization.
                    Department’s telegraphic instructions requested as to whether this meets treaty
                    obligations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kodding</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
